hazard_Name: Landslide - Central Andes, Huaraz, Ancash, Peru
description:
A Landslide Warning has been indicated by the Landslide Hazard Assessment Model (LHASA) on February 7, 2025, 00:40:00 UTC for Central Andes, Huaraz, Ancash, Peru. Landslide Warnings indicate a significant risk of rainfall induced landslide. 

It is estimated that 1.32 Million people, 381,000 households, and $21.0 Billion of infrastructure* are within the affected area(s). *The cost represents the total replacement value of the infrastructure.

Affected areas include: Ancash, Ucayali, Lima, Huánuco, Cajamarca, Junín, Cusco, Amazonas, Huancavelica, La Libertad, San Martín, Pasco and Loreto
